page.title: 10General Occupations, Woking.
page.content: The occupations of Woking residents are varied. Many professional people live in the area. Parents of girls in this school include locally practising architects, solicitors, doctors and dentists. Light industries and many market gardens border the area. The James Walker factory makes packing materials and provides employment as do the many factories on the Sheer- water Estate. A newly built Business Park is as yet unused. The multiracial population help to run the municipal services and local shops. Several tyre and exhaust centres and other specialised motoring and electrical firms exist in the densely populated area between the canal and Maybury Road. The frequent fast trains to London make Woking an important Commuter area and the railway itself provide employment of various kinds.
